702027f.title: Bronx: Washington Avenue - 189th Street (East)
702027f.text:
Washington Avenue, east side, between E. 189th Street and
E. Fordham Road, showing the Powell Farm House. The southwest sec-
tion of Theodore Roosevelt High School now (1939) occupies the
site.
About 1905

702028f-a.title: Bronx: Washington Avenue - 189th Street (East)
702028f-a.text:
Washington Ave., east side, between East 189th Street and East
Road, showing the Powel Farm House, considered to be the oldest ho
in Fordham. Randall Comfort designates the location as East Fordh
Road and Washington Ave., which corresponds with the location give
Kelley's Historical Guide to New York. The above location is with
William Powel estate according to E. Robinson's map of 1885. Howe
the Newell S. Brown map of Westchester County of 1851 shows a Powe
house at what is now (1937) the N.E. corner of Lorillard Place and
Ave. (4434-4436 Third Ave). The site of the Powel House is now oc
by the Theodore Roosevelt High School.
1905.
Gift of Randall Comfort.
